        "id": 1000008
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-11T21:48:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I looked at this more closely.\n1. I agree that the cause is more important than the boot device, so you can ignore comment.\n\nHaving actually look at discoverLastRebootCause for the first time, it does make me wonder if we don\u0027t really need the pinhole reset event that you had previously removed.\n\n@geissonator@yahoo.com do you think we should still emit that pinhole reset event if there\u0027s also a new RebootCause one that contains that info?\n\n2. Yea, we have redundancy, interesting idea to add that.",
      "parentUuid": "26d33619_1b6804a6",
      "revId": "eb49b51aec543932362b65ed44de2eb0702f6f82",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
